/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:10:- The example families already bias the search toward three particular lenses: graph closure, leakage ratio, and delayed-threshold behavior. Those are not neutral. `interaction-graph closure` is likely too combinatorial and basis-sensitive; `leakage-ratio closure` quietly presupposes a norm, normalization, and threshold choice; `delayed-threshold behavioral closure` risks hard-coding Tao's averaged mechanism back into the object.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:11:- The step asks for support, normalization, time window, and spectator size, but it omits several quantities that exact NS actually cares about: phase information, helical sign pattern, amplitude hierarchy, and whether "support" means single modes, conjugate pairs, or packets. That omission matters because triadic forcing depends on more than a support graph.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:21:- The chain mixes true symmetries with bookkeeping conventions. `rescaling` is not a harmless cosmetic move unless the full NS scaling, including time and viscosity normalization, is specified. `conjugate completion` is not cosmetic either; for real-valued velocity fields it changes what the packet literally is. `packet regrouping` can change nonlinear bookkeeping in a way that is mathematically substantive, not merely presentational.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:24:- `helical basis choice` is especially slippery here. If the definition is attached to exact mode interactions, basis dependence may reflect a bad representation choice that should be fixed by canonicalization, not a reason to kill the object entirely.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:34:- Requiring a finite interaction table or finite leakage metric biases the search toward toy notions. A serious exact-NS obstruction may only emerge for a family of packets or a scale-separated construction.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:35:- The phrase "without hidden asymptotic limits" is fair as an anti-handwaving check, but too absolute. Some asymptotic family may be the only honest way to state near-closure quantitatively.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:36:- A delayed-threshold mechanism is specifically time-sensitive. If the chain refuses any definition that needs a nontrivial finite time horizon or a parameter family, it may rule out the most Tao-relevant formulations by design.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:45:- The listed edge cases all come from the inherited non-isolability narrative: Beltrami cancellation, mirror-mode completion, near-degenerate triads, tiny trigger modes. Those are relevant, but they are not a balanced adversarial set.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:46:- Missing are edge cases favorable to the opposite conclusion: carefully engineered helical sign patterns, scale-separated packets, sparse triad geometries, or constructions where leakage is present but dynamically negligible. Without those, the audit is not an attack on the definition space; it is mostly an attack on definitions that do not already agree with the prior mission's intuition.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:70:- The chain overstates the need for representation invariance. For this mission, a theorem object may be perfectly acceptable if it is tied to a canonical Fourier/helical presentation. Full robustness under all regroupings is a luxury standard, not obviously the right one.
