/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- The score mixes fundamentally different requirements: sign pattern, channel separation, rotor dominance, spectator leakage, and delayed-threshold behavior. Those are not obviously commensurable. A scalar score can hide the fact that one catastrophic failure is being compensated by two cosmetic wins.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:18:- The worst item is the "delayed-threshold proxy." Delayed abrupt transfer is a dynamical phenomenon created by coupled evolution, stiffness, and timescale separation. Treating it as a pre-dynamics score feature is a recipe for misranking candidates.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:20:- The score is vulnerable to representation dependence unless Chain 04 has already frozen the invariant object. Phase conventions, packet regrouping, normalization, and helical bookkeeping can all move a candidate's apparent "likeness" without changing the mathematics.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The chain says "full conjugate completion," which is necessary but not sufficient. The real burden is exact closure under all forced interactions, not just mirror completion. Once that is imposed honestly, the "small family" may stop being small.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:42:- "Discard candidates that fail immediately on signs, forced feedback, or overwhelming spectators" sounds crisp but is actually ambiguous. Overwhelming relative to what: coefficient size, initial amplitude, one activation window, or net energy flux?
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:124:The right way to view it is: if Chain 04 first freezes a stable, representation-invariant notion of near-closure, then Chain 03 can become a valuable stress test against that object. Without that gate, it mostly searches for a high score on its own surrogate. And even in the best case, a small exact survivor should be treated as serious anti-obstruction evidence, not an automatic clean kill of the firewall idea.
