`Template-Defect Near-Closure`
and
`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
survive as
`stable after canonicalization`,
while
`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`
survives as
`use-case-limited but honest`.
Mission control therefore keeps the current chain active. The next unresolved
bottleneck is no longer definition sharpness or robustness discipline. It is
whether those surviving notions still say something real when forced onto
explicit normalized exact packets and parameter families, including both
anti-circuit and pro-circuit cases.

## This Step Covers

This strategizer execution covers **Chain Step 4 only**.

You must do all of the following, and only the following:

- test the three surviving candidates:
  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`,
  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`,
  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`;
- choose explicit normalized exact packets or explicitly parameterized packet
  families on the frozen one-bridge role-labeled helical packet object;
- include both anti-circuit and pro-circuit examples;
- include adverse cases already known to matter:
  `Beltrami cancellation`,
  `mirror-mode completion`,
  `nearly degenerate triads`,
  and
  `tiny trigger modes`;
- include cases favorable to the opposite conclusion:
  `engineered helical sign patterns`,
  `sparse triad geometries`,
  `scale-separated packets`,
  and families where leakage exists but may be dynamically negligible;
- precommit quantitative pass/fail criteria for each candidate before reading
  off outcomes;
- use hard admissibility filters and retain a non-aggregated diagnostic vector
  for each candidate on each tested family;
- decide for each candidate whether the exact-packet dossier says
  `survives`,
  `fails`,
  or
  `remains ambiguous`,
  with one named reason;
- decide whether Chain Step 5 is now well-posed as a single honest repair pass,
  or whether the branch instead stops here with the sharpest earned negative
  memo.

Do **not** run the Step-5 repair pass yet. That belongs to Chain Step 5. Do
**not** reopen broad planning or substitute a new candidate family. Minimal
normalization choices are allowed only if they are frozen before outcomes and
kept inside the Step-1 through Step-3 packet discipline.

