# Exploration 001 Summary - Freeze The Step-4 Normalized Test-Family Ledger

## Goal

- Freeze the Step-4 burden currency before any anti-circuit or pro-circuit
  outcomes are read off for:
  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`,
  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`,
  and
  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`.
- Name the anti-circuit and pro-circuit packet families, then freeze one
  normalization sheet, one admissibility-filter set, one pass/fail sheet, one
  diagnostic-vector policy, and one no-retuning rule for the later dossiers.

## What I Tried

- Read the cited Step-2 and Step-3 results, the prior exploration reports, the
  exact-NS Tao-circuit screening notes, the Beltrami fragility note, and the
  tiny-trigger note.
- Checked whether the local record already contained a sharper Step-4 family
  replacement than the menu slots
  `F_BM`,
  `F_DT`,
  `F_SS`,
  `F_SL`.
- Froze one normalized window/currency sheet, wrote hard admissibility filters,
  and fixed candidate-by-candidate thresholds and retained diagnostic vectors.

## Outcome

- `[INFERRED]` `succeeded`.

## One Key Takeaway

- `[INFERRED]` Step 4 can proceed on the original four-family menu, but only
  after freezing one exact normalized forcing ledger and one explicit
  non-retunable threshold sheet.
  The local record had the candidate formulas already, but it had **not** yet
  frozen the Step-4 family grid or the numeric pass/fail sheet.

## Frozen Result

- `[VERIFIED]` Anti-circuit families kept:
  `F_BM`,
  `F_DT(delta, eta_C)`.
- `[VERIFIED]` Pro-circuit families kept:
  `F_SS`,
  `F_SL`.
- `[INFERRED]` Shared normalization sheet frozen:
  amplitude anchor `|A_n(0)| = 1`,
  phase anchor `arg A_n(0) = 0`,
  role-ordered sign-sheet convention,
  mandatory conjugate completion,
  normalized window `I = [0, 1]`,
  and the common forcing ledger
  `(D_on, D_off)`.
- `[INFERRED]` Hard admissibility filters frozen:
  live on-template production,
  frozen packet/spectator sheet,
  full desired plus classwise spectator ledger,
  explicit itinerary trace for positive itinerary claims,
  frozen family grid,
  and `family empty` rather than family drift when a frozen favorable family
  cannot be realized.

## Leads Worth Pursuing

- Compute the exact helical coefficient/sign ledger for `F_DT(1/16, 1/256)` and
  `F_DT(1/8, 1/128)` first, because that family is the cleanest anti-circuit
  stress case that is still dynamically live.
- In the pro-circuit dossier, test `F_SS` before `F_SL` because `F_SS` is the
  cleaner favorable finite-support witness; `F_SL` should then show whether
  scale separation adds anything without changing the burden currency.
- Treat `F_BM` as a negative control and admissibility screen, not as a serious
  positive witness candidate.

## Unexpected Findings

- `[INFERRED]` `mirror-mode completion` is not a detachable extra burden.
  It is already mandatory bookkeeping for every family, so `F_BM` only makes
  that inherited burden dynamically central.
- `[INFERRED]` The local record reached Step 4 without ever freezing numeric
  thresholds.
  This exploration is the first place where the branch writes an explicit
  family/threshold ledger rather than only symbolic candidate formulas.

## Computations Worth Doing Later

- Exact wavevector/helicity tables for the frozen families on the normalized
  one-bridge packet object.
- Exact desired-channel and classwise spectator forcing traces on `I = [0, 1]`.
- Exact `Delta_tmpl`,
  `Delta_spec`,
  `L_tot`,
  `L_class`,
  and
  event-time traces for each frozen family point, with no threshold retuning.

